news.title: SRA flat scam chargesheet filed in Mumbai, former mayor not in it
news.para: Sources said the 500-page chargesheet names BMC officers Sanjay Lokhande, Sanjay Kamble and alleged tout Chandrakant Chavan who have been booked under the relevant IPC sections for cheating and forgery.

news.title: China developers' debt risks persist after support policies' slow start
news.para: China's largest developer by sales said it repaid its 4.75% dollar bonds with outstanding principal totalling $625 million. The payment was due on Tuesday.

news.title: China aims to stabilise housing prices, strictly curb speculation
news.para: China will make more targeted efforts to support demand for owner-occupied and improved housing to boost market confidence, according to China Construction News, led by the Ministry of Housing and Urban-Rural Development.

news.title: Funds for constructing houses may be enhanced in Goa
news.para: Chief minister Pramod Sawant said that the government will make all efforts to make the scheme available and to ensure that the budget allocation is increased.

news.title: Ludhiana improvement trust to float tenders soon for Atal Apartments scheme
news.para: ​The process of issuing letters to successful applicants will be initiated. Officials feel that since it has been a long time since cost estimate of the project was prepared, there are chances of the cost having risen.

news.title: Vizianagaram aims to complete 34,000 housing units by March 2023
news.para: ​While works on 18,320 units were already completed, the remaining are in various phases of execution. As there are hardly two months for Ugadi, the beneficiaries have expedited the works.

news.title: Show cause notices to Ultratech Cement plant for environment norm violation
news.para: The National Green Tribunal (NGT) has directed SPCBs to levy and recover environmental compensation from violating units.

news.title: PMLA court issues fresh arrest warrant against Faith Builders' owner
news.para: Last week, the ED officials had visited residential premises of Tomar to execute the warrant issued in an alleged money laundering case. As Tomar was not found home, the warrant was handed over to his wife on Thursday.

news.title: Malls, brands at loggerheads over rent hikes
news.para: While discussions have started, industry insiders said large retailers are opposing the move given the number of stores they operate. Malls typically sign nine year agreements with the retailers with a rental hike of 15% every three year. But by increasing the rent 5% each year, retailers will have to shell out about 17% in lease cost in three years.

news.title: DB Group deputy MD buys bungalow in Delhi's Golf Links for Rs 75 crore
news.para: According to documents accessed by Zapkey.com, Agarwal paid ₹3.75 crore in stamp duty for the transaction, which was registered in November 2022.

news.title: Proposal on TDS relief on property sold for recoveries under review
news.para: Section 194-IA of the Income Tax Act mandates that TDS, at the rate of 1%, be deducted from the consideration for the transfer of an immovable property if it exceeds ₹50 lakh. Lenders have represented to the government for keeping such sales out of the purview of TDS.

news.title: Abhinandan Lodha Group to invest over Rs 11,000 crore to acquire, develop land parcels
news.para: Of the planned deployment, one-third or over Rs 3,500 crore will be spent on acquisition of land parcels spread over at least 3,000 acres in key locations, while the balance funds will be utilised for development and operations.

news.title: Gurugram: CBI takes over probe in Chintels Paradiso collapse; developer booked
news.para: ​The Haryana government had transferred the case to the CBI on July 18, 2022, which was forwarded to the CBI by the Centre on December 29 last year, they said.

news.title: House prices in South Korea suffer worst fall in at least 19 years
news.para: That follows a 1.37% loss in November and marked a 4.68% decline for 2022, turning around from a 9.93% gain in 2021, the board said in a statement.

news.title: Nashik civic body starts snapping water connections of defaulters
news.para: NMC officials said they have disconnected the water supply lines of 80 defaulters and the remaining disconnections will be done in phases.
